PROJECT REPORT

TITLE:
Medical Appointment No-Show Prediction & Demand Forecasting System

---

1. INTRODUCTION
Healthcare organizations often face challenges due to patient no-shows, which lead to inefficiencies in scheduling, resource utilization, and revenue loss. This project aims to analyze medical appointment data and build a predictive system to identify patients likely to miss appointments. It also provides demand forecasting insights to improve hospital planning and operations.

---

2. OBJECTIVE
The main objectives of this project are:
- To predict whether a patient will attend or miss an appointment
- To analyze factors influencing patient no-shows
- To forecast demand across different hospital departments
- To build an interactive dashboard for visualization and decision-making

---

3. DATASET DESCRIPTION
The dataset contains historical patient appointment records including demographic, medical, and scheduling information. Key features include age, specialty, place, appointment shift, and no-show status.

---

4. DATA PREPROCESSING
Data preprocessing steps included:
- Handling missing values using median and mode
- Encoding categorical variables
- Creating new features such as:
  - age_group
  - health_risk_score
  - is_weekend_shift
- Converting target variable into binary format (1 = No-show, 0 = Show)

---

5. EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA)
EDA was performed to understand patterns in the dataset:
- Distribution of no-show vs show appointments
- Age group impact on attendance
- Specialty-wise patient distribution
- Effect of health risk on appointment behavior

Visualizations helped identify key trends influencing patient behavior.

---

6. MACHINE LEARNING MODEL
A Random Forest Classifier was used to predict patient no-shows.

Input Features:
- Age
- Specialty
- Place
- Age Group
- Health Risk Score
- Appointment Shift

Output:
- 1 → Patient will not attend appointment
- 0 → Patient will attend appointment

The model learns patterns from historical data to make predictions.

---

7. DEMAND FORECASTING
Demand analysis was performed to understand hospital workload patterns:
- Specialty-wise patient distribution
- Age group-based demand
- Location-based patient visits

This helps hospitals allocate staff and manage scheduling efficiently.

---

8. DEPLOYMENT
The solution was deployed using Streamlit, which provides an interactive web-based interface for users to:
- View analytics dashboard
- Predict patient no-shows
- Analyze demand patterns

---

9. CONCLUSION
The system successfully combines machine learning and data analytics to improve healthcare operations. It helps reduce patient no-shows and enhances hospital resource planning through data-driven insights.

---

10. FUTURE SCOPE
- Improve model accuracy using hyperparameter tuning
- Add time-series forecasting for demand prediction
- Deploy on cloud platforms
- Integrate SMS/email reminder system for patients